2. Bias versus lag
  • 14 replications of fixed OR (1, 1.2, 1.4, 1.5, 2, 5) and N (2000) with varying lag. I.E. of the 14 replications, only lag varies.
  • In each of these 14 replications, 100 systems are considered and 2 credible sets (using ordered and non ordered) are produced.
  • Hence, there are 14*200 simulations.
  • Notice for OR=5, most ordered CS only have one variant (the causal, as expected).

3. rmvbin function
  • Want to use this function to simulate haplotypes, incorporating info on LD.
  • Will replace simref function.
  • Once this is up and running our simulations will represent real-world data more.
  • We can then supply this as an argument to the wrapper2() function and repeat the analysis.
install.packages("bindata")
nsnps <- 100
nhaps <- 1000
maf <- runif(nsnps,0.05,0.5)
haps <- rmvbin(nhaps,maf) # haplotypes given the probability for each snp
                          # how can we incorporate LD????
snps <- colnames(haps) <- paste0("s",1:nsnps)

# want to write a function something like below

simref <- function(nsnps=100, nhaps=1000, ld=someLDmatrix){
  rmvbin(nhaps,bincorr= someLDmatrix) # uses matrix of binary correlations
  OR
  rmvbin(nhaps,sigma = someLDmatrix) # covariance matrix for the normal distribution
  OR
  rmvbin(nhaps,commonprob = someLDmatrix) # matrix of probabilities that components i                                             and j are simultaneously 1.
}
